(secondQuint)Pinloc Versus Hansson Pins in the Treatment of Femoral Neck Fractures.

.

 Patients, who are to be treated with internal fixation due to a femoral neck fracture, will be randomized by the surgeon to Pinloc or Hansson Pins using an on-line randomization system.

 The patients will be followed up at open visits at 3 months and 1 year.

 At two years the patients will be contacted by phone and medical records studied in order to detect any fracture complications.

